<TEXT>
egypt is combining old photographs 
and american high technology in the most comprehensive 
savethesphinx campaign in 3400 years 
such an ambitious project was last undertaken in ancient egypts 
new kingdom after legend has it a young prince fell asleep in 
the shadow of the sphinx and heard it whisper save me 
the new campaign announced this week by culture minister farouk 
hosni follows years of delay and disagreement over how to save the 
crumbling monument a halfman halflion sculpted 4600 years ago 
the egyptian antiquities organization launched an emergency 
conservation project last year to remove and replace concrete 
blocks and mortar from the sphinxs front paws and haunches 
the new project combines the egyptians restoration work with 
modern monitoring equipment from the united states to discover why 
the sphinx is deteriorating and what to do about it 
protective wooden scaffolding already climbs from the statues 
chest to the top of its cobraadorned headdress the famous 
piercing eyes and subtle smile barely show through 
i must find a way to save it said sayed tawfik egyptian 
antiquities chairman inspecting the monument tuesday not just 
for my lifetime but for the next 2000 years 
tawfik contacted the getty conservation institute which 
provided the monitoring equipment the marina del ray calif 
institute will pay about 200000 for a year of monitoring and pick 
up some of the preservation costs 
people institutions everybody was afraid to touch the 
sphinx afraid theyd be blamed if something went wrong tawfik 
said we have a nickname for it father of terror everybody 
was terrified to help us because the sphinx is so big and so 
famous 
luis monreal the getty institutes director said hes ready 
for the challenge 
you have to imagine that although the sphinx has been around 
almost 5000 years its been covered with sand for all but about 
500 he said since the sphinx was last uncovered in 1925 it 
has been exposed to the modern world 24 hours a day 
we cannot return the sphinx to the way it would have looked to 
the pharaohs but we are confident we can return it to the pristine 
look it had in 1925 if thats the look the egyptians want 
a 200pound 6foottall meteorological station will be perched 
atop the sphinxs back anchored by sandbags capable of recording 
data for one year the solarpowered monitor will record traffic 
vibrations changes in moisture temperature and wind direction and 
the effects of sand salt water and earthquakes 
erosion has gutted almost every part of the mammoth limestone 
statue and experts predict the decay will increase dramatically as 
cairos 14 million population continues to expand 
the first major campaign to save the sphinx was the project of 
the young prince who later became pharaoh tuthmosis iv asleep in 
the shadow of the sandcovered sphinx traditon holds that he saw 
the beast come to him in a dream and heard its promise to lead him 
to the throne if he would free it 
after he became pharaoh tuthmosos had his artisans restore the 
statue about 1400 years later greeks and romans also repaired 
the sacred sphinx with small blocks similiar to those the egyptians 
are inserting today 
monreal said his team has gathered the available literature on 
the sphinxs history including all restoration attempts and ideas 
on how to save it 
he has collected photographs from as early as the mid1800s 
when only the sphinxs head protruded from the sand he said the 
pictures will enable the team to create a computer model of what 
has happened when what could happen and what can be done about it 
the important thing monreal said is the egyptians have 
decided the sphinx must be saved we agree 
</TEXT>
