his tummy 
the mummy was unwrapped and sliced open a year later in the 
universitys archaeology lab the tubes showed traces of organic 
matter leading the scholars to conclude that bits of organs 
removed from the body during mummification had been sewn back to be 
reunited with the body in the afterlife 
inscriptions on the bandages and other evidence led to the 
conclusion that the mummy had been a scholar and a member of 
egypts priestly class who died in his early 20s 
since then the mummy had been wrapped in plastic and stored in 
a wooden crate after its surprise appearance in abels room it 
was returned to its climatecontrolled resting place in a campus 
building 
