markets said realtors president norman d flynn who also noted 
that the beginning of a year is generally a slow home sales period 
nar chief economist john a tuccillo said a big increase in 
sales is unlikely in the coming months because of the mortgage 
rates but added that as rates taper off in the spring we expect 
sales to pick up mainly in markets offering moderately priced 
homes 
