<TEXT>
jewelry store manager bob husman says he 
had no idea he was in the path of a killer tornado right until 
the time the roof fell on my head he wonders if better radar 
would have saved an employee 
in fact this north alabama city was so shaken by the 20 deaths 
caused by the nov 15 storm that officials want to pay 120000 to 
upgrade the radar at the local office of the national weather 
service 
the weather service says no thanks 
federal officials plan to close the huntsville office and more 
than 100 others while installing the 450 million next generation 
weather radar dubbed nexrad 
huntsville officials worry they wont be close enough to nexrad 
units to benefit from the advanced technology but the system is 
eagerly awaited in other parts of the southeast that have been 
blindsided by killer storms 
people are not being warned in time said gil patrick a 
meteorologist for walbtv in albany ga in nearby colquitt county 
two people were killed oct 1 by a tornado unseen by the nearest 
weather service radar in columbus ga 
patrick thinks planned nexrad units in atlanta jacksonville 
fla and tuskegee will help southwest georgia 
north carolinas congressional delegation is pushing for the 
earliest possible installation of nexrad in raleigh an unexpected 
tornado killed four people in the eastern part of the state nov 
28 1988 while the weather radar unit in raleigh was awaiting 
repair 
the new system scheduled to be complete by 1996 can follow the 
movement of moisture in the air the current system can only 
measure how much moisture is present meteorologists say the 
improvement will allow them to identify tornadoes before they 
descend earthward 
it holds the promise of increasing the lead time for tornado 
warnings from the current average of three minutes to as much as 30 
minutes said curtis stanford a staff member of the house 
subcommittee that oversees the weather service 
the extra time would have been precious to husman in addition 
to the employee who died husman and four others were hurt when the 
golbro jewelry store was demolished by the huntsville tornado 
thirty minutes would have made a great deal of difference in 
what we could have done he said we couldnt have done much to 
save our business but we could have done something to prevent 
death and injury 
the day of the storm husman heard news reports about the 
possibility of severe weather but the warnings were no more 
serious than we get with normal thunderstorms 
certainly there was no thought of immediate danger right 
until the time the roof fell on my head 
the weather service issued a tornado warning as the storm hit 
the tornado killed 20 injured 463 and drove 500 people from their 
homes it also called sharp attention to the weather services 
proposal to put the closest nexrad units in birmingham and in 
nashville tenn each about 100 miles from huntsville 
blair conrad of the huntsvillemadison county airport authority 
said the weakpoint of the weather service plan is that nexrads 
capability to measure speed and direction of moisture in the air 
diminishes beyond about 70 miles 
don sarreals assistant to the director of the nexrad program 
office acknowledges the curvature of the earth prevents the radar 
beams from picking up loweraltitude funnels more than 92 miles 
away but the weather service contends nexrad can spot telltale 
cyclone patterns that occur at altitudes of 10000 feet to 15000 
feet within 125 nautical miles 
gary petti of the weather services birmingham office said a 
nexrad unit in huntsville might have missed the november tornado 
because of its close range 
the weather service has 249 offices including 52 fully staffed 
forecasting offices said sarreals the agency plans to shut down 
small offices and reorganize into 113 fully staffed offices plus 
13 river forecast centers 
the services 113 nexrad units will work in conjunction with 24 
to be run by the pentagon 
while congress has been enthusiastic about nexrad many members 
are concerned that some of the planned office closings are 
motivated as much by the need for budget cuts as the advent of the 
new radar stanford said 
a provision in the federal budget this year prohibits the 
closing of any weather station unless the weather service first 
puts into place the nexrad unit and runs tests to show the affected 
area will not suffer a loss in service 
