<TEXT>
getting lots of potassium is no substitute for 
taking high blood pressure medicines according to a report being 
published in thursdays new england journal of medicine 
researchers studied 287 middleage men already on medication for 
high blood pressure and put half on potassium and half on placebos 
then their regular blood pressure medicines were withdrawn 
during the next two years the men took the potassium or dummy 
supplements and followed lowsalt diets about half the people in 
both groups had to resume taking blood pressure pills because of 
rising blood pressure 
the researchers said their work suggests that potassium 
supplementation does not reduce the need for antihypertensive 
medication of men on a lowsodium diet 
the study was suggested by population research that found groups 
with high levels of potassium in their diets also tend to have 
healthy blood pressures 
</TEXT>
