scientists have created a substance that blocks 
infection by viruses that cause colds a possible step toward drugs 
that could prevent or ease up to 45 percent of all colds 
but one of the studys authors steven marlin cautioned that it 
was done in the test tube and speculating on its meaning for a 
human cold is a huge leap 
in the study scientists decoyed coldcausing rhinoviruses into 
attaching themselves to a freefloating manmade version of a 
molecule that the viruses normally bind to on the surfaces of 
healthy cells thus diverting the viruses from their normal target 
by this process researchers found the manmade molecule was 
largely able to block rhinovirus infection of human cells in the 
test tube 
the research is presented in thursdays issue of the british 
journal nature 
