<TEXT>
the head of a major abortion clinic on wednesday 
hailed the governments decision to subsidize abortions performed 
with the controversial ru 486 pill and said it would not increase 
the number of pregnancies terminated in france 
the government announced this week that the cost of the 
procedure would be reimbursed under the national health care 
program which covers most medical and dental care costs in france 
were very pleased with the decision which weve been 
expecting for some time said dr elisabeth aubeny chief of the 
abortion clinic at the broussais hospital in paris 
but it wont increase the number of abortions performed in 
france because the decision to terminate a pregnancy is not a 
question of money its because the patient has no other choice 
she said in a telephone interview 
under a decree signed monday by health minister claude evin 
women undergoing druginduced abortions will be reimbursed 80 
percent of the actual cost of 246 
the pill procedure costs only slightly more than other types of 
abortion which have been legal in france since 1975 and have been 
partially covered by the national health care program since 1983 
the ru 486 pill or mifepristone invented by french researcher 
etienneemile beaulieu for the rousseluclaf pharmaceutical 
company was first authorized for use in september 1988 
however roussel pressured by antiabortion activists in europe 
and the united states withdrew it from the market the government 
then ordered the company to resume distribution 
the pill known under the brand name mifegyne has been 
distributed widely in france free of charge but the company said 
wednesday it will now be marketed commercially it is not for sale 
elsewhere 
dr aubeny predicted more women would turn to the ru 486 a 
safer and simpler alternative to traditional methods of abortion 
there are both physical and psychological advantages to using 
the abortion pill it avoids the many complications that go with 
surgery and anesthesia and makes patients feel more involved in the 
procedure she said 
the pill a synthetic hormone compound works by blocking the 
action of progesterone a hormone essential in all stages of 
pregnancy researchers say ru 486 is especially effective in the 
early stages of pregnancy 
there are 793 centers throughout france that distribute the 
pill about 20000 women have had druginduced abortions 
the ru 486 is not a doityourself morningafter pill that can 
be purchased over the counter and taken at home it is dispensed 
only in governmentapproved hospitals and clinics where patients 
are screened for potential physical and psychological problems 
three appointments are needed spread over a sevenday period as 
required by french law first patients take three tablets of 
mifepristone simultaneously two days later they receive an 
injection of the hormone prostaglandin which produces contractions 
to dislodge the fertilized egg 
dr aubeny said the egg is usually expelled within 12 hours at 
broussais hospital patients receive their injections in the 
morning and spend the rest of the day under observation 
the procedure is followed by a checkup including an ultrasound 
test to make sure the pregnancy has been terminated 
there were 162960 abortions performed in france in 1988 
figures for 1989 have not been released 
</TEXT>
