<TEXT>
samuel r mozes a former city planner and 
prominent figure in international jewish affairs has died of a 
heart attack he was 66 
mozes died feb 21 at his home in east hampton on long island 
he was director of the bureau of urban affairs in the state 
division of housing and community renewal from 1959 to 1975 for 
seven years before that he worked in the citys department of 
planning 
he was instrumental in developing the states 1960 housing code 
which became a prototype for other cities and oversaw 
comprehensive rezoning of staten island 
born in warsaw poland mozes fled with his family from the 
nazis in 1939 and arrived in america in 1941 after stops in 
lithuania and japan 
from 1941 to 1951 he was associate editor of the overseas 
jewish news agency he was executive director of the world 
gathering of holocaust survivors in israel in 1981 and in 
washington in 1984 
mozes received a bachelors degree in architecture and a 
masters in urban planning and housing from columbia university he 
held a doctorate in environmental science from columbia pacific 
university 
mozes taught in recent years at long island university and 
columbia 
he is survived by his wife janine two sons and a sister 
