decisions 
also wednesday lawmakers in annapolis md conducted a hearing 
on four abortion restriction bills and one prochoice bill the 
hearing attracted an overflow crowd that left about 150 people 
mostly abortion opponents standing with protest signs outside a 
legislative building 
in minnesota waldorf tried unsuccessfully to have the measure 
taken up in the house first he had predicted the bill would lose 
on a tie vote in the senate committee because the committee had 
been stacked against the bill by majority leader roger moe who 
supports abortion rights 
the house health and human services committee held hearings on 
