aboard eastern flight 103 ap its breakfast time on a 
weekday morning new yorkto atlanta flight and the youthful cabin 
crew is serving up some corporate boosterism along with the 
rewarmed scrambled eggs 
easterns name is built on their reputation said a 
21yearold flight attendant who identified herself as melody she 
said that reputation drew her to take her first job as a flight 
attendant three months ago after working in the restaurant business 
flight 103 out of new yorks laguardia airport is nearly full 
the passengers a mix of business travelers and leisure fliers but 
even the new enthusiasm doesnt help the boeing 727 buck the lineup 
of planes waiting to take off the 905 departure isnt airborne 
until 935 
melodys colleagues on the flight carlos cardenas and cody 
fulmer also are young enthusiastic and relatively new to eastern 
they are the flip side of the bitter strike against eastern which 
began a year ago and threw thousands of pilots flight attendants 
and machinists out of work 
for the newcomers the dispute that pitted the unions against 
eastern owner frank lorenzo was an opportunity 
i wanted to become a flight attendant so bad said cardenas 
23 who before the strike had worked for eastern in bogota 
colombia as a ticket agent and reservation agent 
as part of lorenzos costcutting strategy the airline has 
hired thousands of new employees at lower pay to replace the union 
strikers many of the replacement workers are young single 
without families and mortgages to support and not especially 
receptive to trade unionism 
eastern flight attendants for example now earn an average 
1688 a month down from 2029 before the strike 
its just like any other job youve got to work your way 
up melody replied when asked if she resented the relatively low 
wages 
insiders estimate that the new employees have cut about 10 years 
off the average age of easterns work force of 20000 from the 
mid40s to the mid30s the minimum age for eastern flight 
attendants is 18 
even the uniforms for flight attendants are new navy blue with 
gold stripes on the sleeves described as a more professional look 
replacing the old khakicolored outfits and red scarves female 
attendants also wear a militarystyle kepi reminiscent of 
stewardess uniforms in the mid1950s some say the jaunty caps make 
them an easy target for the jeers of machinist pickets at airports 
breakfast on flight 103 is scrambled eggs hash brown potatoes 
tiny sausages orange juice and a small blueberry muffin in first 
class its fancier and includes an omelette and fresh fruit salad 
in the cockpit theres a mix of eastern veterans and newcomers 
the captain jon mcclure has flown for eastern 22 years he 
stayed out for six months before crossing the picket line to return 
to work 
mcclure is flying this trip with copilot phil gibson 42 and 
flight engineer dan marouf 34 both hired after the strike started 
i wanted to get this company going i wanted to be part of a 
team said gibson who had flown corporate jets for five years 
before joining eastern last june im not here for the short 
term i plan to make this a career 
mcclure calling the strike illconceived said that now 
new and old pilots are working well together and all the employees 
are hustling more than before asked about easterns future 
prospects he gazed out the cockpit window at a distant point 
im optimistic but it could go either way 
</TEXT>
