<TEXT>
harold poling begins a threeyear term as 
chairman of ford motor co on thursday a stint some analysts say 
appears to be a caretaker role while the next chairman is groomed 
for office 
the 64yearold poling who is vice chairman and chief operating 
officer succeeds donald petersen 63 as chairman and chief 
executive 
petersen and poling have worked closely for the past decade 
during which ford changed from a struggling overweight giant that 
lost 15 billion in 1980 to a much leaner company that earned an 
industry record 53 billion eight years later 
the relatively limited time poling will head the company is 
considered unusual by management standards 
its often the case when there has been some kind of trauma 
said edward bowman deputy dean of the university of pennsylvanias 
wharton school the especially unusual thing about it is that 
ford is in especially good shape 
bowman who concentrates his research on chief executive 
positions said the ford board of directors election of poling to 
a limited term as chairman would imply that they werent quite 
ready in terms of succession planning that they werent ready to 
name somebody else for a normal term 
most of the speculation for a longerterm chief executive 
officer in the mid1990s and beyond has centered on allan gilmour 
a ford executive vice president who on thursday adds the title of 
president of the ford automotive group 
petersen joined ford in 1949 and held a variety of positions in 
domestic and international product planning design and marketing 
before he became president polings ford career began in 1951 and 
focused mainly on the financial side of the corporation 
petersen has been credited with freeing designers and engineers 
in the early 1980s to work together in developing the ford taurus 
and mercury sable cars of the mid1980s which helped lift ford 
from the financial doldrums 
i really think that petersen made the necessary adjustments in 
the product plan auto analyst charles brady of oppenheimer amp co 
of new york the key addition he made was to leave product 
planning to the product planners 
poling would do well to follow that lead brady said 
i think hes got to challenge product planners with the 
charge that this is a very intensely competitive game he said 
thats all hes got to do in the product area 
bowman said i think he poling would be a nut in that 
threeyear period to mess with any product decisions 
poling has his work cut out for him 
the us auto industry is in the depths of a recession that 
began in october companies are wrestling with a way to wean 
american consumers from rebates and other incentives that have 
become ingrained in car buying and are eroding profits 
each of the nations big three automakers general motors corp 
ford and chrysler corp are taking steps to eliminate costs and 
steamline operations with gm and chrysler imposing plant shutdowns 
and layoffs 
brady said poling can leave his mark by raising productivity at 
ford 
if he can follow through with the productivity increase while 
the programs continue in the petersen manner it will be one of the 
best onetwo punches of all time brady said 
poling will become the fourth company chairman who was not a 
member of the ford family the two fords now in company management 
are cousins william c ford jr 32 who heads the companys 
marketing staff and edsel ford ii 41 directors of heavy truck 
engineering and manufacturing both are greatgrandsons of company 
founder henry ford 
