investigation after the 1987 market crash haas securities a 
brokerage house collapsed nine days after the crash 
the prosecution maintained that the firms scheme to 
artificially raise the prices of penny stocks inexpensive 
securities traded over the counter couldnt be maintained after 
the market dropped and the share prices fell 
laff was convicted of being part of a scheme to artificially 
inflate the penny stock prices by creating a false demand for the 
shares and then selling out his firms own stake before the prices 
collapsed 
