third quarter including a 95 million writeoff in its publishing 
business 
in explaining the debt ratings reduction moodys boted that 
repayment of the companys bank debt with proceeds from the theme 
parks sale had reduced harcourts interest costs substantially 
it said the company should have enough cash flow to service its 
cash interest charges and capital spending over the near term 
because of the deferred cash payment features of some of its debt 
instruments 
but moodys added it is uncertain that the company will be 
able to achieve the growth necessary to service its debt and 
preferred stock once all fixed charges are payable in cash 
the agency noted that the market value of assets can change and 
said the aftertax proceeds from sale of harcourt assets at a 
given point in time may not be sufficient to cover both debt and 
preferred securities 
