<TEXT>
the former parent of imperial savings 
association sought bankruptcy protection just days after the thrift 
was seized by federal regulators who said it was 601 million in 
the red 
the government took control of imperial savings last week in 
large part because of problems brought about by its large portfolio 
of junk bonds 
imperial had invested more than 97 billion of its assets in 
junk bonds junk bond prices have plummetted in recent months and 
thrifts must divest their holdings by 1994 under provisions of last 
years savings and loan bailout legislation 
only columbia savings and loan in beverly hills has a bigger 
portfolio of the highyield highrisk bonds among thrifts 
imperials former parent imperial corp of america said 
wednesday it had filed for chapter 11 protection in bankruptcy 
court in san diego to protect its other subsidiaries 
the filing will give it breathing room to come up with a 
reorganization plan without having to worry about creditors 
lawsuits 
this was a very difficult decision said ica chief executive 
lyman hamilton however in an effort to protect our bondholders 
shareholders and continue our operating businesses we believe this 
was a prudent thing to do 
imperial corp and its former savings and loan subsidiary 
effectively split friday when the thrift was taken over by the 
resolution trust corp the federal agency that manages seized 
thrifts accounts up to 100000 are federally insured 
todays filing by imperial corp in now way affects imperial 
savings or its depositors savings because the two are now 
independent companies imperial savings spokesman kenn ulrich 
said 
imperial corp will be forwarding documentation of its assets 
and liabilities to the court over the next few weeks said patrick 
shea a lawyer for the firm representing the corporation in the 
proceedings 
ulrich said he didnt know what imperial corps other 
subsidiaries were and didnt have any of its financial data 
available because he started his job just two weeks ago 
